# ArchArena — Cursor Rules
# System design interview practice SaaS
# Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) · TypeScript · Tailwind · tldraw · Socket.io · Zustand · Anthropic SDK · Prisma · PostgreSQL · Redis

# ============================================================
# PROJECT CONTEXT — READ FIRST
# ============================================================
# This is a SaaS product where users practice system design
# interviews on a collaborative whiteboard. The AI interviewer
# has full context of the drawing (as a semantic graph — NOT
# raw tldraw JSON), the chat history, and the active prompt.
#
# Key architectural decisions already made:
# - tldraw canvas → parsed into SemanticGraph (nodes + edges)
#   before ANYTHING is sent to AI. Never send raw tldraw JSON.
# - Two AI models: claude-haiku for hints (fast, cheap),
#   claude-sonnet for final scoring (strong, thorough).
# - Free tier: ephemeral, IndexedDB is source of truth on client.
#   Redis (TTL 2h) on server. No Postgres for free users.
# - Pro/Premium tier: Postgres for metadata, R2/S3 for JSON blobs.
# - Socket.io for persistent connection. Client debounces 1.5s
#   and diffs the graph before emitting — never send unchanged state.
# - Zustand for all session state. No prop drilling.
# - Vendor-specific tldraw custom shapes with ShapeMeta.
#   Each shape carries: vendor, category, label, isLabeled.
# - Unlabeled arrows → red border + exclamation badge. Never block the user.
# - No auth in Week 1-2. Everything is hardcoded free tier limits.

# ============================================================
# TYPESCRIPT
# ============================================================
- Always use strict TypeScript. No `any` unless absolutely unavoidable —
  if you must use `any`, add a comment explaining why.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases.
- All shared types live in `src/types/index.ts`. Never define
  one-off types inline in components — add them to types first.
- Use `as const` for static lookup objects (e.g. VENDOR_CATALOGUE).
- Never use non-null assertion (`!`) without a comment. Prefer
  explicit null checks or optional chaining.
- Avoid enums — use string union types or `as const` objects instead.

# ============================================================
# NEXT.JS APP ROUTER
# ============================================================
- Every component that uses hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers
  must have `"use client"` at the top. Default to server components
  for everything else.
- API routes live in `src/app/api/`. Each route exports only
  `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` — named exactly like that.
- Never put business logic directly in route handlers. Extract to
  `src/lib/` functions and call them from the route.
- Always return typed responses. Use `NextResponse.json()` for
  JSON, `new Response()` for streams.
- Streaming responses (scoring endpoint): use `ReadableStream`
  with `TextEncoder`. Never buffer the full AI response.
- Environment variables: server-only vars (API keys) have no
  `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix. Client vars must have it. Never mix these.

# Payments (LemonSqueezy)
# - initLemonSqueezy() must be called before any LS API call
# - Webhook secret lives in LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# - Never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars for secret operations
# - Variant IDs are public — safe for NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
# - Always verify webhook signature before processing
# - Tier changes ONLY happen via verified webhooks, never
#   via direct API calls from the client
# LemonSqueezy webhook setup:
# 1. Go to LemonSqueezy dashboard → Settings → Webhooks
# 2. Add endpoint: https://yourdomain.com/api/billing/webhook
# 3. For local dev use ngrok: ngrok http 3000
#    Then add: https://[ngrok-url]/api/billing/webhook
# 4. Select these events:
#    - order_created
#    - subscription_created
#    - subscription_updated
#    - subscription_cancelled
#    - subscription_expired
# 5. Copy the signing secret to LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# NEVER expose LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET to the client
# NEVER skip signature verification in the webhook handler

# Auth variables (never hardcode these anywhere):
# DATABASE_URL — Supabase PostgreSQL connection string
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET — random 32-byte base64 string  
# NEXTAUTH_URL — full app URL including protocol
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID / GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET — from Google Cloud Console
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET — from GitHub Developer Settings
# These are server-only — none have NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
# Client code must never import or reference these directly

# ============================================================
# AI / ANTHROPIC SDK
# ============================================================
- NEVER send raw tldraw records to the AI. Always pass through
  `parseCanvasToGraph()` first and send the `SemanticGraph`.
- Two models, two purposes — do not swap them:
    Hints / chat  → claude-haiku-4-5-20251001  (max_tokens: 150)
    Final scoring → claude-sonnet-4-6          (max_tokens: 800)
- Scoring prompt must instruct the model to respond ONLY in valid
  JSON matching the `ScoreResult` type. Parse defensively.
- Hint prompt: one question or observation, max 2 sentences.
  The prompt must explicitly say "don't reveal the full answer."
- Always check free tier limits BEFORE making any AI API call.
  Return `{ error: "free_limit_reached" }` with status 403 if exceeded.
- Keep prompt builders in `src/lib/ai.ts`. Never write prompt
  strings inside components or route handlers.

# ============================================================
# TLDRAW & CANVAS
# ============================================================
- Never import from `@tldraw/editor` directly — use `@tldraw/tldraw`.
- Custom shapes live in `src/components/canvas/shapes/`.
  Each shape file exports a `ShapeUtil` subclass + a type alias.
  All custom shapes are registered in `shapes/index.ts`.
- Every custom shape MUST read `props.meta.isLabeled` and render
  a red border + exclamation badge when false. This is not optional.
- The default tldraw toolbar is hidden. `VendorToolbar` is the
  only way users add shapes. Do not re-enable the default toolbar.
- `CanvasWatcher` is the only place that reads from `editor.store`.
  It debounces 1500ms and calls `hasGraphChanged()` before propagating.
  Never bypass this — direct store reads elsewhere cause performance issues.
- `parseCanvasToGraph()` in `src/lib/graph-parser.ts` is the single
  source of truth for canvas → AI translation. If you need canvas
  data anywhere, use this function.

# ============================================================
# STATE MANAGEMENT (ZUSTAND)
# ============================================================
- All session state lives in `src/store/session.ts`. One store, one file.
- Never use React Context for session state — that's Zustand's job.
- Hints and chat messages are separate concepts:
    `hints[]`    → background AI observations, shown on demand
    `messages[]` → explicit user ↔ AI conversation
  Never mix them into the same array.
- `updateLastMessage()` is for streaming — it patches the last item
  in the messages array in place. Use it only for streaming responses.
- Usage counters (`hintsUsed`, `scoresUsed`) must be incremented
  BEFORE the API call, not after. This prevents double-firing on retries.

# ============================================================
# SOCKET.IO
# ============================================================
- All socket logic goes through `src/lib/socket-client.ts`.
  Never import `socket.io-client` directly in components.
- The socket connects lazily on `joinSession()` call.
  Do not auto-connect on app load.
- Client emits: `canvas:update`, `session:join`
  Server emits: `hint:new`
  Do not add new event names without updating this list here.
- Free tier: socket is used for hint delivery only.
  Pro tier (Week 3+): also used for collaborative session sync.

# ============================================================
# INDEXEDDB (FREE TIER PERSISTENCE)
# ============================================================
- All IndexedDB operations go through `src/lib/indexeddb.ts`.
  Never call `indexedDB` directly in components.
- Save on every canvas change (debounced with canvas watcher).
- For free tier users, IndexedDB is the source of truth.
  If the session is not found in Redis, the client recovers from IndexedDB.
- Keys: `session:{id}` → `{ graph, notes, savedAt }`

# ============================================================
# DATABASE
# ============================================================
- Always import prisma from `@/lib/prisma` 
  Never import PrismaClient directly anywhere else
- Never instantiate new PrismaClient() in any file
- All DB queries go through API routes or 
  server actions — never in client components

# ============================================================
# COMPONENTS
# ============================================================
- Component folders mirror the domain:
    canvas/     → tldraw + shapes + toolbar + validation
    chat/       → AI chat panel, messages, input
    score/      → score display, breakdown, missed concepts
    notes/      → markdown notes textarea
    prompt/     → selector on homepage, badge in session
    session/    → timer, layout, export button
    ui/         → shared primitives (Button, Badge, Modal)
- One component per file. File name = component name (PascalCase).
- No barrel `index.ts` re-exports in component folders —
  import directly from the file to keep traces readable.
- Keep components dumb where possible. Business logic belongs in
  `lib/` or the Zustand store, not inside JSX.
- Session layout: canvas is `flex-[3]`, right panel is `flex-[2]`.
  Right panel splits vertically: notes top, chat bottom. Do not
  change these proportions without discussing it first.

# ============================================================
# STYLING
# ============================================================
- Tailwind only. No inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components.
- Dark theme throughout. Background: `gray-950`. Panels: `gray-900`.
  Borders: `gray-800`. Never use white backgrounds in the session page.
- Validation state colors:
    Unlabeled shape/arrow → `border-red-500`, badge `bg-red-500`
    Labeled              → `border-blue-400` (database), `border-green-400` (cache), etc.
- Free tier limit nudge: amber banner (`bg-amber-900/30 border-amber-600`).
  Upgrade CTA is placeholder text for now — no links until Week 3.
- Use `group` and `group-hover` for toolbar submenus. No JS-driven hover state.

# ============================================================
# FILE NAMING
# ============================================================
- Components: PascalCase (`InterviewCanvas.tsx`)
- Lib / utils: kebab-case (`graph-parser.ts`, `socket-client.ts`)
- Store: camelCase (`session.ts`)
- Types: camelCase (`index.ts`)
- API routes: always `route.ts` inside a descriptively named folder

# ============================================================
# ERROR HANDLING
# ============================================================
- All `fetch()` calls must check `res.ok` before reading the body.
- AI API errors must surface a user-friendly message in the chat panel —
  never silently fail or log to console only.
- Free limit errors (403 `free_limit_reached`) must show the upgrade
  nudge UI, not a generic error message.
- IndexedDB operations: always wrap in try/catch. Failure is non-fatal —
  log a warning but don't block the session.
- Never let a failed hint request interrupt the drawing flow.
  Hints are best-effort, not blocking.
